    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_002676_0001" n="0001"/>
<opener>
<lb/><add place="margintop" rend="right" hand="#U">35</add> <dateline rend="right"><placeName><settlement type="town">Tette</settlement></placeName> <date when="1856-03-04">4 March 1856</date></dateline>
<lb/>
<lb/>Alfredo Duprat <choice><abbr>Esqu.</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice> 
<lb/><salute>My dear Sir,</salute>
</opener>

<lb/><p>Having reached this the farthest
<lb/>inland station at present occupied
<lb/>by the <term type="people">Portuguese</term> on the morning
<lb/>of the 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> current, I was received
<lb/>with the usual politeness and generosity
<lb/>of your nation. The <term type="occupation">governor</term> kindly
<lb/>proposed to send an express forward
<lb/>to <unclear cert="medium"><persName>Senna</persName></unclear> with letters and I have
<lb/>been constantly employed in writing
<lb/>ever since. The enclosed you will see
<lb/>is intended to show the <persName><term type="occupation">King of
<lb/>Portugal</term></persName> <!-- Could this be more accurately encoded as <term type="occupation">? JM --><!-- We can have both! AW -->my gratitude by giving
<lb/>him the earliest intelligence of my
<lb/>discoveries. I cannot be sure whether
<lb/>it will be acceptable or not, but on
<lb/>reading it you will see I avoid the
<lb/>appearance of intrusion by saying
<lb/>that no answer is expected; and
<lb/>indeed if it only reaches his eye, I hope
<lb/>for no more. Even though he may not
<lb rend="right"/>have


	<pb facs="liv_002676_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>have <choice><sic>leizure</sic><corr>leisure</corr></choice> to look into it, the          	
<lb/>attention of an influential minister
<lb/>may be attached to some of the
<lb/>points mentioned, and even this
<lb/>will be so far good.</p> 
            	
<lb/><p>I hope you have received
<lb/>my note about the "berryman". It
<lb/>would prove a real boon to <placeName><country>Angola</country></placeName>.
<lb/>But the enclosed will give you
<lb/>some information so I need not
<lb/>enlarge. This is a magnificent
<lb/>river. I hope to ascend it with
<lb/>my family to within one or two
<lb/>degrees off <placeName><settlement type="village"><persName>Sekeletu</persName></settlement></placeName> by means of
<lb/>flat bottomed boats. And it is
<lb/>a magnificent country too; but
<lb/>trade is ruined by "Caffre <!--Either Caffir or Coffee...I can't tell which. -AA --><!-- It is Caffre, as I have corrected it. JM --> wars".	
<lb/>The natives rob, so there are no
<lb/>goods here for trade. A man
<lb/>named <persName>Nyaode</persName> living on an
<lb/>island below this, takes what
<lb/>and as much as he likes - out of
<lb/>every boat that ascends. There
<lb rend="right"/>is</p>

	<pb facs="liv_002676_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/><p>There is a fine bed of coal close to
<lb/>this on the surface almost, and
<lb/>superior iron too. What fools! not
<lb/>to have a small flat bottomed
<lb/>steamer flying between this and 
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="village"><persName>Senna</persName></settlement></placeName>. Two swivels would keep
<lb/>off all robbers and in six months
<lb/>her price would be paid. The only
<lb/>impediments I have seen besides
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="fissure">Monoatunya</geogName></placeName> are insignificant
<lb/>rapids which would not delay the <term type="tribe">Makololo</term> a day.</p>
            	
<lb/><p>Wait a little, we shall see,
<lb/>if we live. I have had excellent
<lb/>health all the way down here,
<lb/>but am very thin and tired from
<lb/>marching on foot; but will soon
<lb/><unclear cert="low">r---</unclear>.</p>

<lb/><p>I often remember my <w>obliga-
<lb break="no"/>-tions</w> to your kind recommendations.
<lb/>May God bless and reward you, is
<lb/>the sincere wish of</p>
<closer>
<lb/><salute>your <choice><abbr>obedt</abbr><expan>obedient</expan></choice></salute>
<lb/><signed><choice><abbr>Sigt</abbr><expan>Signature</expan></choice> <persName>David <choice><orig>Livingston</orig><reg>Livingstone</reg></choice></persName></signed>
</closer>


            </div>
